<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="776" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0090/2158a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-02">September 2,
                                        1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2154. Exchange vessel <hi rend="italic">Gripsholm</hi> sailed from
                                New York<note n="20" xml:id="d776fn20">With 1430 tons of food
                                    parcels and other relief cargo and 5528 pieces of
                                    luggage.</note> for Marmagão via Rio de Janeiro, Montevideo and
                                Port Elizabeth as scheduled on September 2 at 7 a.m. Safe
                                    conduct<note n="21" xml:id="d776fn21">For text of announcement
                                    of safe conduct, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, October 16, 1943, p. 256.</note> assured by
                                all belligerents.</p>
                            <p>Please request Swiss Government to inform Japanese Government for its
                                information and information of all other enemy governments.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>